{
  "stem": "11067.2",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "That's why I've always, I'd always tried to lose the English accent later on-- tried to lose the German accent.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And little by little, German faded into almost nonexistence with me.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It did-- just nonexistence.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It was, was almost a mental block, so that it was only English.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The ones in Coventry.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I knew about three or four of them.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I still have-- no, no, no-- ah well, originally.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I'm talking about the-- those that were, that were with the families in Coventry.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were always in touch, because they were with Christadelphian families so we met at social situations.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Even the families socialized, too.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And so we met under those kind of situations.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But I had a lot of English friends all the time, both in the village of Cuddington where I stayed and in Coventry.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the time was divided that I was in Coventry during the summer time, when the rains were not bad, and I was in the country in the winter time.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Always concerned.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I mean, the stuff that was in the newspapers-- and as I said, it was very vivid because we had the bombings, too.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then the bombings in, in Germany that we, you know, knew about.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I mean, we knew as soon as Britain bombed Germany we were going to get it the next night.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There was just no question.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We knew exactly when we were going to get a big one, because it was, you know, tit for tat kind of thing that went on.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "My foster mother's brother-in-law was part of D-day and got badly wounded.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "D-day was June 6th, 1944, and I was 13 years old.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
